res” have shaped the existence of Caribbean people while calling for a reassessment of what political liberation might look like.Duke University Press Scholars of Color First Book Award recipient  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aArt, CaribbeanxSocial aspects. 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etczCaribbean Area. 0aGaysxLegal status, laws, etc.zCaribbean Area. 0aHomosexualityzCaribbean Area. 0aHuman beingsxAnimal nature. 0aQueer theory. 0aSex and art. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074331908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2021z9783110753783oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147802188940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478021889423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478021889/original  a978-3-11-074331-9  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075403-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DADb2021